1 (a) The state shall not be liable for providing reimbursement to the federal
2 government; and
3 (b) The qualifying hospitals that received a state-directed payment under this
4 section shall be liable for all reimbursement that may be owed to the federal
5 Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services or any other federal agency;
6 and
7 (6) The department shall promulgate administrative regulations in accordance with
8 KRS Chapter 13A to implement the programs[program] described in this section.
9 Section 2. If the Medicaid preprint required to be submitted under subsection
10 (2) of Section 1 of this Act is approved by the federal Centers for Medicaid and Medicare
11 Services with a retroactive effective date of January 1, 2026, the Department for
12 Medicaid Services shall, upon receipt of approval from the federal Centers for Medicare
13 and Medicaid Services, direct each Medicaid managed care organization with which the
14 department has contracted for delivery of Medicaid services to make retroactive
15 enhanced add-on payments to qualifying hospitals for any previously paid Medicaid
16 claims for physician and nonphysician professional services provided to a Medicaid
17 beneficiary on or after January 1, 2026, by the qualifying hospital's affiliated physician
18 groups or physicians or other professionals employed by or contracted with the qualifying
19 hospital.
